[Transported to a laboratory for testing within 24 hours of sample collection presumably means results will be transmitted by telephone within 48 hours, so that suspected cases with negative tests will not have to be kept in hospital longer than that, taking up bed space. This is a considerable advance, 1st reported in last week's WHO sitrep. - Mod.JW]

******
[2] Sierra Leone: Cuban doctor tests positive, evacuated to Switzerland
Date: 19 Nov 2014
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/11/19/us-health-ebola-cuba-idUSKCN0J308820141119


A Cuban doctor treating Ebola patients in Sierra Leone has tested positive for the disease and was being sent to Geneva for treatment, officials said, the 1st Cuban known to have contracted the potentially deadly hemorrhagic fever.

The doctor ... is one of 165 Cuban doctors and nurses treating Ebola patients in Sierra Leone. They have been there since early October [2014].

They are part of a Cuban team of 256 medical professionals sent to West Africa to treat patients in the worst Ebola outbreak on record that has killed more than 5000 people.

[Byline: Daniel Trotta]

