[4] Liberia: One in 2 workers now jobless
Date: 19 Nov 2014
Source: BBC News [edited]
http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-30119043


Nearly half of all Liberians who were employed when the Ebola outbreak began are no longer working, a survey by the World Bank has found. It said many workers have been told to stay at home or have lost their jobs, while markets have been forced to shut. Earlier, a World Bank economist said the Ebola outbreak was expected to cost the region about USD 3-4 billion (GBP1.9-2.5 billion)... - more

